22/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament Speaker Ljupco Jordanovski on Sunday (21 November) dismissed the possibility of a political crisis in the country, saying he expects the new government to start work by the end of December.
In an interview with Radio Free Europe, Jordanovski said the legislature continues to function normally despite the resignation of Prime Minister Hari Kostov's cabinet, adding that there are no signs of instability in the ruling coalition.
Also Sunday, the ruling Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia accepted municipal nominations for a new leader, prior to Wednesday's party congress.
In all, ten candidates were nominated to the post.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 22/11/04;
A1 TV, Dnevnik, Vest - 21/11/04)
